{"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol\/pushThreadDefault()"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","isActive":true},{"text":"-based I\/O) which are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"started in this thread to run under ","type":"text"},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"changes the context returned by [func"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"affect the context used by functions like [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.idle_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextprotocol\/pushthreaddefault()"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"thread, passing it a [struct","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] which will be run by a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"ever call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"], assuming you want","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the new [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the thread.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"cycle is managed by a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":"), it is always suggested to wrap"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"text":"] inside a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] \/"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"] pair, otherwise threads that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"] reference they hold."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronous operation inside a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"] pair, but it is up to you to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"started while the non-default context is active.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","title":"pushThreadDefault()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE17pushThreadDefaultyyF"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainLoop":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mainloop","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainLoop","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"representing the main event loop of a GLib or GTK application.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainLoop","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","title":"MainLoop","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainLoop","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"ThreadPool","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextProtocol":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContextProtocol"}],"title":"MainContextProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainContext"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MainContextProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextprotocol","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContextProtocol/pushThreadDefault()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Acquires "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes the context returned by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"type":"text","text":"], so it does not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"title":"pushThreadDefault()","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContextProtocol\/pushThreadDefault()","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontextprotocol\/pushthreaddefault()","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"../gio/index.html":{"url":"..\/gio\/index.html","type":"link","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","title":"Gio","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gio"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"title":"MainContext","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"}}}